The input `pizza` is a rectangular matrix with dimensions `rows x cols`.
The elements of `pizza` are characters, either `'A'` (an apple) or `'.'` (empty cell).
The input `k` is an integer.
`k` is greater than or equal to - `rows` and `cols` are greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to - `rows` is equal to the length of `pizza`.
`cols` is equal to the length of `pizza[i]` for all `i` in the range of `0` to `rows-1`.
`pizza` consists only of characters `'A'` and `'.'`.
